05/12/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police arrested at least ten suspected terrorists during several raids in Athens on Saturday (December 4th), seizing weapons and explosives. "This is a case that the police have been following for some time now and the operation is still at its early stages," police spokesman Athanasios Kokalakis said. He only identified one of the areas where a raid was conducted -- the suburb of Nea Smyrni. Local media said that other sites included downtown Athens, the neighbourhood of Exarchia and the port of Piraeus. (AP, ANA-MPA - 04/12/10)
